trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of key/value pairs that are sorted by key based on the associated <see cref="T:System.Collections.Generic.IComparer`1" /> implementation.
trans-unit.target: 表示基于相关的 <see cref="T:System.Collections.Generic.IComparer`1" /> 实现按键进行排序的键/值对的集合。

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> generic class is an array of key/value pairs with O(log `n`) retrieval, where n is the number of elements in the dictionary.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>泛型类是与 O 键/值对的数组 (日志`n`) 检索，其中 n 是字典中的元素的数目。

trans-unit.source: In this, it is similar to the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> generic class.
trans-unit.target: 在中，它是类似于<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>泛型类。

trans-unit.source: The two classes have similar object models, and both have O(log `n`) retrieval.
trans-unit.target: 两个类具有类似的对象模型，并且都具有 O (日志`n`) 检索。

trans-unit.source: Where the two classes differ is in memory use and speed of insertion and removal:
trans-unit.target: 两个类的不同之处是在内存使用和的插入和删除的速度：

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> uses less memory than <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> 使用较少的内存比<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> has faster insertion and removal operations for unsorted data, O(log `n`) as opposed to O(`n`) for <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> 具有更快的插入和删除操作未排序的数据，O (日志`n`) 而不是 O (`n`) 为<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>。

trans-unit.source: If the list is populated all at once from sorted data, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> is faster than <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>.
trans-unit.target: 如果从已排序的数据，在一次填充列表<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>比快<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>。

trans-unit.source: Another difference between the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602> and <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> classes is that <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> supports efficient indexed retrieval of keys and values through the collections returned by the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.Keys%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.Values%2A> properties.
trans-unit.target: 另一个区别<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedDictionary%602>和<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>类在于<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>支持的键和值通过返回的集合的有效索引的检索<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.Keys%2A>和<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.Values%2A>属性。

trans-unit.source: It is not necessary to regenerate the lists when the properties are accessed, because the lists are just wrappers for the internal arrays of keys and values.
trans-unit.target: 不需要时重新生成列表属性可以访问，因为列表是内部数组的键和值的只是包装器。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> is implemented as an array of key/value pairs, sorted by the key.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> 实现为键/值对，排序的键的数组。

trans-unit.source: Each element can be retrieved as a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602> object.
trans-unit.target: 每个元素都可以作为<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>对象。

trans-unit.source: Key objects must be immutable as long as they are used as keys in the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>.
trans-unit.target: 密钥对象必须是不可变，只要它们是否用作中的键<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>。

trans-unit.source: Every key in a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> must be unique.
trans-unit.target: 中的所有键<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>必须是唯一的。

trans-unit.source: A key cannot be `null`, but a value can be, if the type of values in the list, `TValue`, is a reference type.
trans-unit.target: 密钥不能为`null`，但值则可以为，如果在列表中，值的类型`TValue`，为引用类型。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> requires a comparer implementation to sort and to perform comparisons.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> 需要进行排序并执行比较的比较器实现。

trans-unit.source: If not, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Comparer%601.Default%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> checks whether the key type `TKey` implements <xref:System.IComparable?displayProperty=nameWithType>.
trans-unit.target: 如果没有，<xref:System.Collections.Generic.Comparer%601.Default%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>检查是否键类型`TKey`实现<xref:System.IComparable?displayProperty=nameWithType>。

trans-unit.source: If the key type `TKey` does not implement either interface, you can specify a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IComparer%601?displayProperty=nameWithType> implementation in a constructor overload that accepts a `comparer` parameter.

trans-unit.source: The capacity of a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> is the number of elements the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> can hold.
trans-unit.target: 容量<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>是元素的数目<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>可以保存。

trans-unit.source: As elements are added to a <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>, the capacity is automatically increased as required by reallocating the internal array.
trans-unit.target: 如元素添加到<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>，自动增加容量通过重新分配在内部数组所需的方式。

trans-unit.source: The capacity can be decreased by calling <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.TrimExcess%2A> or by setting the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.Capacity%2A> property explicitly.
trans-unit.target: 可以通过调用减少容量<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.TrimExcess%2A>或通过设置<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602.Capacity%2A>属性显式。

trans-unit.source: Decreasing the capacity reallocates memory and copies all the elements in the <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>.
trans-unit.target: 减少容量重新分配内存并将复制中的所有元素<xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602>。

trans-unit.source: For very large <xref:System.Collections.Generic.SortedList%602> objects, you can increase the maximum capacity to 2 billion elements on a 64-bit system by setting the `enabled` attribute of the configuration element to `true` in the run-time environment.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.

trans-unit.source: The dictionary is maintained in a sorted order using an internal tree.
trans-unit.target: 字典将保留在使用内部树的排序顺序。

trans-unit.source: Every new element is positioned at the correct sort position, and the tree is adjusted to maintain the sort order whenever an element is removed.
trans-unit.target: 每个新元素都位于正确的排序位置，并对树进行调整以维护排序顺序，只要移除元素。

trans-unit.source: While enumerating, the sort order is maintained.
trans-unit.target: 枚举，时维护排序顺序。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: At this position, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，未定义 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，在读取 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 的值之前，必须调用 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> 将枚举器向前移动到集合的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> returns the same object until <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 返回相同的对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> to the next element.

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: You cannot set <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again; you must create a new enumerator instance instead.
trans-unit.target: 无法再次将 <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerator%601.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素；必须改为创建新的枚举器实例。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in C++, `For Each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: `foreach` C# 语言的语句 (`for each` c + + 中`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中) 隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 也会将枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，未定义 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，在读取 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 的值之前，必须调用 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> 将枚举器向前移动到集合的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> 或 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 返回同一对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IDictionaryEnumerator.Entry%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举数没有对集合的独占访问权；因此，从头到尾对一个集合进行枚举在本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.source: Default implementations of collections in <xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType> are not synchronized.
trans-unit.target: 集合中的默认实现<xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType>不同步。

trans-unit.source: Returns an enumerator that iterates through a collection.
trans-unit.target: 返回循环访问集合的枚举数。

trans-unit.source: An <see cref="T:System.Collections.IEnumerator" /> that can be used to iterate through the collection.
trans-unit.target: 可用于循环访问集合的 <see cref="T:System.Collections.IEnumerator" />。

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in C++, `For Each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: `foreach` C# 语言的语句 (`for each` c + + 中`For Each`在 Visual Basic 中) 隐藏了枚举数的复杂性。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 因此，建议使用 `foreach`，而不是直接操作枚举数。

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 枚举器可用于读取集合中的数据，但不能用于修改基础集合。

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 最初，枚举数定位在集合中第一个元素的前面。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 也会将枚举器放回此位置。

trans-unit.source: At this position, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 在此位置上，未定义 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>。

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 因此，在读取 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 的值之前，必须调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 将枚举器向前移动到集合的第一个元素。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 在调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 或 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 之前，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 返回同一对象。

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为下一个元素。

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 如果<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>越过的末尾的集合，枚举数定位在集合中的最后一个元素的后面和<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 当枚举器位于此位置上，后续调用<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>还返回`false`。

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果最后一次调用到<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>返回`false`，<xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 若要再次将 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> 设置为集合的第一个元素，可以调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 并接着调用 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>。

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 只要集合保持不变，枚举数就保持有效。

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and its behavior is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 如果对集合进行更改（如添加、修改或删除元素），则枚举数将失效且不可恢复，而且其行为是不确定的。

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 枚举数没有对集合的独占访问权；因此，从头到尾对一个集合进行枚举在本质上不是一个线程安全的过程。

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can lock the collection during the entire enumeration.
trans-unit.target: 若要确保枚举过程中的线程安全性，可以在整个枚举过程中锁定集合。

trans-unit.source: To allow the collection to be accessed by multiple threads for reading and writing, you must implement your own synchronization.
trans-unit.target: 若要允许多个线程访问集合以进行读写操作，则必须实现自己的同步。

trans-unit.source: Default implementations of collections in <xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType> are not synchronized.
trans-unit.target: 集合中的默认实现<xref:System.Collections.Generic?displayProperty=nameWithType>不同步。
